<segment id="1" parent="1001" relname="preparation">Build a Better Relationship with Your New Stepchild</segment>
<segment id="2" parent="1002" relname="preparation">So you just got married .</segment>
<segment id="3" parent="1002" relname="joint">That 's great !</segment>
<segment id="4" parent="5" relname="condition">If your new spouse has children already</segment>
<segment id="5" parent="1004" relname="span">then you ’re also a new stepparent .</segment>
<segment id="6" parent="1007" relname="span">Stepchildren can be a blessing and a curse</segment>
<segment id="7" parent="6" relname="condition">depending on your relationship ,</segment>
<segment id="8" parent="1008" relname="same_unit">and</segment>
<segment id="9" parent="1010" relname="condition">if you ’re reading this article ,</segment>
<segment id="10" parent="11" relname="attribution">you probably feel</segment>
<segment id="11" parent="1010" relname="span">it ’s a curse .</segment>
<segment id="12" parent="1012" relname="contrast">It may seem difficult now ,</segment>
<segment id="13" parent="1012" relname="contrast">but with help and time , you may start to get along .</segment>
<segment id="14" parent="1014" relname="span">Read this article</segment>
<segment id="15" parent="1015" relname="span">to start the journey</segment>
<segment id="16" parent="15" relname="elaboration">of building a better relationship with your new stepchild .</segment>
<segment id="17" parent="1017" relname="preparation">Steps</segment>
<segment id="18" parent="1019" relname="span">Think of why he may be acting the way</segment>
<segment id="19" parent="18" relname="elaboration">that he is .</segment>
<segment id="20" parent="1021" relname="question">Is he uncomfortable with the relationship ?</segment>
<segment id="21" parent="1022" relname="span">Perhaps you said something to him</segment>
<segment id="22" parent="21" relname="elaboration">that he took the wrong way ?</segment>
<segment id="23" parent="1024" relname="span">Did you marry his mother right</segment>
<segment id="24" parent="23" relname="circumstance">after causing the death of his father ?</segment>
<segment id="25" parent="1026" relname="span">These are all good questions</segment>
<segment id="26" parent="1027" relname="span">to ask yourself</segment>
<segment id="27" parent="1028" relname="joint">in trying to assess your relationship</segment>
<segment id="28" parent="1028" relname="joint">and understand your new step son .</segment>
<segment id="29" parent="30" relname="condition">Since you are new to the child ,</segment>
<segment id="30" parent="1030" relname="span">let them set the pace of the relationship .</segment>
<segment id="31" parent="1032" relname="span">Younger children may be quicker to bond with you ,</segment>
<segment id="32" parent="31" relname="concession">while older children may be more reluctant to get close .</segment>
<segment id="33" parent="1034" relname="span">Do n’t force them to become close to you ,</segment>
<segment id="34" parent="33" relname="manner">as you cannot force trust or love .</segment>
<segment id="35" parent="1037" relname="attribution">Remember</segment>
<segment id="36" parent="1037" relname="joint">that you are not their real parent</segment>
<segment id="37" parent="1038" relname="span">and that they will still feel devoted to the biological parent</segment>
<segment id="38" parent="37" relname="elaboration">that you have replaced .</segment>
<segment id="39" parent="1040" relname="span">They may also only listen to your spouse</segment>
<segment id="40" parent="39" relname="circumstance">before warming up to you .</segment>
<segment id="41" parent="1025" relname="joint">Do not begin calling them “ son ” or “ daughter . ”</segment>
<segment id="42" parent="1043" relname="span">Let the relationship grow</segment>
<segment id="43" parent="42" relname="circumstance">before jumping into that .</segment>
<segment id="44" parent="45" relname="attribution">Do be strong in the household ,</segment>
<segment id="45" parent="1045" relname="span">whether they listen to you or not .</segment>
<segment id="46" parent="1048" relname="attribution">Make sure the stepchild knows</segment>
<segment id="47" parent="1048" relname="joint">that they are to respect you</segment>
<segment id="48" parent="1048" relname="joint">and are not free to do whatever they please .</segment>
<segment id="49" parent="1025" relname="joint">Your spouse should have your back</segment>
<segment id="50" parent="1051" relname="span">and do their best</segment>
<segment id="51" parent="50" relname="purpose">to encourage the child to cooperate .</segment>
<segment id="52" parent="1025" relname="joint">Enforce the rules .</segment>
<segment id="53" parent="54" relname="condition">If they do not listen to you ,</segment>
<segment id="54" parent="1054" relname="span">let them suffer the consequences .</segment>
<segment id="55" parent="1056" relname="contrast">Appropriate punishments would be grounding them</segment>
<segment id="56" parent="1056" relname="contrast">or not letting them do a fun thing .</segment>
<segment id="57" parent="1025" relname="joint">Plotting to kill your stepchild may be too much .</segment>
<segment id="58" parent="1025" relname="joint">Do n’t let your new stepchild feel rejected by you .</segment>
<segment id="59" parent="1025" relname="joint">How you act towards them will seem amplified .</segment>
<segment id="60" parent="61" relname="condition">If you get angry ,</segment>
<segment id="61" parent="1061" relname="span">it will feel stronger than what they receive from their parents .</segment>
<segment id="62" parent="63" relname="attribution">Make sure that your stepchild understand</segment>
<segment id="63" parent="1063" relname="span">why you ’re angry with them .</segment>
<segment id="64" parent="1065" relname="span">Ask them questions</segment>
<segment id="65" parent="64" relname="purpose">to make them feel heard and understood .</segment>
<segment id="66" parent="1025" relname="joint">Children do n’t like to feel unloved ,</segment>
<segment id="67" parent="1025" relname="joint">and they are quick to feel rejected .</segment>
<segment id="68" parent="1025" relname="joint">How you treat them in the beginning can have a huge impact on your future relationship .</segment>
<segment id="69" parent="1069" relname="preparation">Tips</segment>
<segment id="70" parent="1070" relname="joint">Always consider the perspective of the stepchild</segment>
<segment id="71" parent="1070" relname="joint">Do n't be too strict , or too much of a pushover</segment>
<segment id="72" parent="1071" relname="span">Warnings</segment>
<segment id="73" parent="1072" relname="joint">Plotting to kill your stepchild will result in chaos .</segment>
<segment id="74" parent="75" relname="preparation">Do not employ his/her friends as spies .</segment>
<segment id="75" parent="1073" relname="span">This leads to distrust .</segment>
